ught%20I%20would%20do%20my%20aiming%20on%20vacations%20and%20things%20like%20that%2C%20but%20no.%20I%20really%20need%20to%20get%20off%20the%20treadmill%20now%20and%20then%2C%20and%20make%20space%20to%20address%20some%20of%20these%20bigger%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20part%20of%20resetting%20Dropbox's%20approach%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Houston%20said%20is%20now%20focused%20on%20streamlining%20productivity%20%E2%80%94%20was%20taking%20full%20accountability%20for%20the%20struggles%20the%20company%20was%20facing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20look%20at%20this%20and%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20Microsoft%20is%20mean%2C'%20or%20'Google%20was%20mean%2C'%20or%20'Apple%20was%20mean%2C'%20but%20I%20drove%20the%20ship%20towards%20these%20rocks.%26quot%3B%20Houston%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20downside%20of%20being%20a%20founder%2C%20a%20CEO.%20You%20can't%20blame%20the%20last%20guy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArmed%20with%20increased%20self-awareness%2C%20Houston%20said%20he%20worked%20to%20snap%20himself%20out%20of%20a%20funk%20by%20taking%20an%20unflinching%20look%20at%20his%20own%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses.%20It%20changed%20the%20way%20he%20communicated%20with%20his%20employees%20and%20helped%20him%20think%20more%20clearly%20about%20what%20he%20wanted%20to%20produce%2C%20the%20CEO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirst%20it's%20getting%20out%20of%20this%20delusional%20state%20where%20you%20think%20you're%20great%2C%20just%20sort%20of%20splashing%20cold%20water%20on%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20If%20the%20last%20thing%20customers%20have%20seen%20from%20the%20company%20in%20recent%20years%20is%20a%20price%20increase%2C%20then%20'What%20the%20hell%20are%20we%20doing%3F%26quot%3B%20Houston%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20later%2C%20Dropbox%20went%20public.%20Today%2C%20the%20company%20has%20a%20market%20cap%20of%20around%20%249.5%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouston%20also%20had%20some%20words%20of%20advice%20for%20founders%20about%20protecting%20against%20burnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20burnout%20is%20the%20biggest%20thing%20that%20will%20sort%20of%20kill%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20that's%20why%20I%20think%20these%20coping%20methods%20and%20getting%20your%20own%20head%20right%20is%20important.%20But%20if%20you%20do%20that%2C%20it's%20also%20this%20amazing%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChallenge%20is%20not%20optional%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20be%20challenged%2C%20but%20the%20suffering%20is%20optional.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdropbox-ceo-burnout-importance-of-mental-health-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737799381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679422b2eb4be2fff9a224ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdropbox-ceo-burnout-importance-of-mental-health-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Drew%20Houston%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Dropbox%2C%20recently%20shared%20his%20strategies%20for%20tackling%20burnout%20in%20the%20face%20of%20a%20hard%20time%20in%20a%20podcast%20interview.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sperkel%40insider.com%20(Sarah%20Perkel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdropbox-ceo-burnout-importance-of-mental-health-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22For%20'VC%20Twitter%2C'%20LinkedIn%20is%20becoming%20the%20place%20to%20be%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20in%20a%20vest%20holds%20a%20phone%20with%20a%20speech%20bubble%20showing%20the%20LinkedIn%20logo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67912d4510c98eace91371a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption