%3Brooted%20in%20respect%20and%20inclusion%20is%20appropriate%20and%20necessary.%26quot%3B%20Costco%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20BI's%20request%20for%20further%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20half%20of%20US%20residents%20are%20female%2C%20while%20more%20than%2040%25%20consider%20themselves%20non-white%2C%20according%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20USAFacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224a302e3c-072e-4740-b8cd-88db59063514%5C%22%3EActivists%20are%20targeting%20DEI%20programs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20companies%20have%20made%20pitches%20in%20favor%20of%20DEI.%20Apple%20has%20encouraged%20investors%20to%20vote%20against%20a%20shareholder%20proposal%20to%20jettison%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fapple-s-board-recommends-shareholders-vote-against-eliminating-dei-programs-1034217736%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDEI%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20filing%20this%20month%2C%20it%20criticized%20the%20petition%20as%20one%20that%20would%20constrain%20Apple's%20%26quot%3Bability%20to%20manage%20its%20own%20ordinary%20business%20operations%2C%20people%20and%20teams%2C%20and%20business%20strategies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20that%20pressure%20from%20investors%20comes%20as%20activists%2C%20like%20the%20influencer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobby-starbuck-conservative-activist-targeting-companies-dei-policies-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobby%20Starbuck%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20pushed%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20successfully%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-latest-company-walk-back-dei-initiatives-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWalmart%20%E2%80%94%20to%20alter%20their%20programs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Walmart%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20remains%20committed%20to%20%26quot%3Bcreating%20a%20culture%20where%20everyone%20can%20be%20successful%2C%20and%20ensuring%20we%20are%20a%20Walmart%20for%20everyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20vice%20president%20of%20human%20resources%2C%20Janelle%20Gale%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20memo%20this%20month%20that%20the%20parent%20of%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20would%20cease%20to%20have%20a%20team%20focused%20on%20DEI.%20She%20also%20said%20that%20the%20term%20DEI%20had%20%26quot%3Bbecome%20charged%26quot%3B%20because%20it's%20sometimes%20seen%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bpractice%20that%20suggests%20preferential%20treatment%20of%20some%20groups%20over%20others.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Target's%20announcement%20Friday%2C%20Kiera%20Fernandez%2C%20the%20company's%20chief%20community%20impact%20and%20equity%20officer%2C%20wrote%20that%2C%20as%20a%20company%20that%20sees%20millions%20of%20customers%20daily%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20understand%20the%20importance%20of%20staying%20in%20step%20with%20the%20evolving%20external%20landscape.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20that%20shifting%20landscape%2C%20as%20Meta's%20Gale%20noted%20in%20her%20memo%2C%20involves%20what's%20legal.%20That%20reassessment%20follows%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%202023%20decision%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ends-affirmative-action-colleges-decision-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eending%20affirmative%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20college%20admissions.%20While%20it's%20not%20permissible%20to%20practice%20DEI%20in%20a%20way%20that%20becomes%20discriminatory%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20push%20to%20weaken%20DEI%20could%20prompt%20added%20scrutiny%20of%20corporate%20programs%2C%20legal%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%2C%20McDonald's%2C%20and%20Target%20didn't%20respond%20to%20BI's%20requests%20for%20further%20comment.%20Apple%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20an%20inquiry%20sent%20outside%20normal%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20the%20White%20House's%20pushback%2C%20it%20was%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-programs-america-diversity-equity-inclusion-pushback-how-to-fix-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20tough%20political%20environment%20for%20DEI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20critics%20often%20assail%20for%20prioritizing%20gender%20or%20ethnicity%20over%20merit.%20In%20addition%2C%20some%20who%20sympathize%20with%20the%20aims%20of%20DEI%20programs%20contend%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-programs-america-diversity-equity-inclusion-pushback-how-to-fix-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20of%20the%20efforts%20aren't%20effective%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20need%20to%20be%20reimagined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e07d38de-ec3c-4fe0-a79e-69d5caa4ba5f%5C%22%3E'A%20business%20imperative'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20might%20be%20convinced%20to%20stay%20the%20course%20on%20DEI%20because%20such%20efforts%20are%20often%20part%20of%20a%20strategy%20to%20attract%20and%20keep%20the%20best%20workers%2C%20Diana%20Scott%2C%20US%20human%20capital%20center%20leader%20at%20The%20Conference%20Board%2C%20told%20BI.%20The%20Conference%20Board%20describes%20itself%20as%20a%20nonpartisan%2C%20nonprofit%20entity.%20As%20part%20of%20its%20work%2C%20it%20operates%20councils%20for%20business%20leaders%20in%20areas%20including%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20inclusion%2C%20and%20belonging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20execs%20Scott%20talks%20with%20from%20the%20large%20companies%20that%20make%20up%20the%20think%20tank's%20membership%20say%20they%20plan%20to%20continue%20their%20DEI%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20them%2C%20it's%20a%20business%20imperative%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20diverse%20workforce%20where%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20equity%20%E2%80%94%20things%20like%20fairness%20in%20opportunities%20and%20in%20how%20workers%20are%20rewarded%20%E2%80%94%20leads%20to%20better%20culture%20and%20collaboration%2C%20Scott%20said.%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20drives%20innovation%20and%20better%20business%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20view%20this%20as%20a%20zero-sum%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20views%20on%20DEI%20among%20many%20of%20the%20business%20leaders%20she%20talks%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227db90ffd-ffdd-43e3-a142-46818c335172%5C%22%3ESome%20DEI%20efforts%20haven't%20been%20working%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20support%20doesn't%20mean%2C%20however%2C%20that%20there%20aren't%20DEI%20efforts%20that%20couldn't%20be%20improved%2C%20Scott%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20researchers%20agree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIris%20Bohnet%2C%20a%20behavioral%20economist%20at%20Harvard's%20Kennedy%20School%20of%20Government%20and%20coauthor%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BMake%20Work%20Fair%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20some%20measures%2C%20like%20diversity%20training%2C%20too%20often%20fail%20to%20change%20behaviors%20that%20could%20be%20influenced%20by%20bias%2C%20such%20as%20decisions%20on%20hiring%2C%20promotions%2C%20or%20performance%20appraisals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20have%20been%20doing%20in%20the%20past%20five%20to%2010%20years%20really%20hasn't%20been%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20one%20reason%20to%20revisit%20%E2%80%94%20yet%20not%20abandon%20%E2%80%94%20DEI%2C%20Bohnet%20said.%20Focusing%20on%20ideas%20like%20fairness%20could%20create%20greater%20buy-in%20from%20skeptics%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d960cc88-dfa2-4e49-8545-2ebdf36df964%5C%22%3EMany%20workers%20support%20DEI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20some%20employers%20are%20likely%20to%20stick%20with%20DEI%20is%20because%20employees%20often%20support%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20August%20survey%20of%20some%201%2C300%20workers%20and%20executives%20at%20US%20companies%2C%2058%25%20of%20respondents%20told%20the%20Conference%20Board%20that%20their%20organization%20put%20an%20appropriate%20amount%20of%20effort%20into%20DEI.%20About%20one%20in%20five%20workers%20said%20their%20employer%20didn't%20go%20far%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20groups%20that%20have%20historically%20often%20faced%20a%20tough%20time%20on%20the%20job%2C%20DEI%20often%20matters%20a%20great%20deal.%20About%20half%20of%20women%20and%2056%25%20of%20Black%20workers%20told%20the%20Conference%20Board%20they%20wouldn't%20work%20for%20an%20organization%20that%20didn't%20regard%20it%20as%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20these%20companies%20have%20been%20practicing%20DEI%20for%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20performative%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJennie%20Glazer%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20think%20tank%20Coqual%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20barriers%20to%20advancement%20for%20underrepresented%20people%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20its%20members%2C%20which%20include%20big%20companies%20like%20JPMorgan%2C%20believe%20that%20%26quot%3Binclusive%26quot%3B%20workplaces%20are%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDiverse%20teams%20make%20better%20decisions%20and%20solve%20problems%20faster%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20she%20thinks%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20many%20companies%20will%20ultimately%20abandon%20all%20of%20their%20efforts%20in%20this%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20going%20to%20have%20a%20very%20multicultural%20workforce%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20you%20invest%20in%20DEI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-costco-keeping-dei-despite-trump-executive-orders-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737797581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b87a214fb5b23cc5e5402%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-costco-keeping-dei-despite-trump-executive-orders-2025-1%22%2C%22summa