20own%20volition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hugh%20Jackman%2C%20Emma%20Stone%2C%20Aubrey%20Plaza%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792ab232fcded5e90748717%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20brand%20became%20a%20celebrity%20favorite%20in%20the%202010s.%3Cp%3EBobby%20Bank%2FGC%20Images%3B%20Bobby%20Bank%2FWireImage%3B%20Rich%20Fury%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThink%20of%20it%20as%20pre-social-media%20influencer%20marketing.%20Coupled%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20pricing%20that%20firmly%20marked%20the%20brand%20as%20luxury%2C%20it%20worked.%20When%20Dani%20Reiss%20officially%20joined%20the%20company%20in%201997%2C%20annual%20revenue%20was%20about%20%242.2%20million.%20In%202008%2C%20it%20hit%20%2416.4%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Cut%20declared%202015%20%26quot%3Bthe%20winter%20of%20Canada%20Goose%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Vogue%20featured%20A-lister%20after%20A-lister%20wearing%20its%20signature%20jackets.%20The%20company%20now%20had%20fashion%20bona%20fides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20you%20need%20to%20legitimize%20yourself%20by%20proving%20that%20you%20can%20work%20effectively%20and%20that%20you%20can%20bring%20a%20product%20that%20is%20actually%20well-performing%2C%26quot%3B%20Emanuela%20Prandelli%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20fashion%20and%20luxury%20management%20at%20Bocconi%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThen%20you%20can%20cross-cut%20it%20with%20the%20fashion%20luxury%20component.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ae99f6b9-6f69-494e-8417-4f7e1a695fe1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowing%20up%20%E2%80%94%20and%20growing%20beyond%20down%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20went%20public%20in%202017%2C%20and%20its%20stock%20climbed%20steeply%20for%20the%20next%20few%20years.%20But%20that%20momentum%20has%20waned.%20In%20the%20past%2012%20months%2C%20Canada%20Goose%20shares%20have%20fallen%20about%2011%25%3B%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20they're%20down%2070%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20have%20blamed%20several%20factors.%20The%20luxury%20sector%20fell%20overall%20in%202024%2C%20with%20industry%20bellwethers%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flvmh-luxury-louis-vuitton-struggles-china-slowdown-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELVMH%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Kering%20also%20tumbling.%20In%20October%2C%20Wells%20Fargo%20downgraded%20Canada%20Goose's%20stock%20to%20%26quot%3Bunderweight%2C%26quot%3B%20citing%20a%20lackluster%20performance%20on%20social%20media%20and%20overreliance%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhats-behind-china-luxury-goods-slowdown-economy-changing-consumer-tastes-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20where%20it%20has%20the%20most%20retail%20stores%20and%20which%20produces%20the%20most%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20facing%20economic%20instability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20Canada%20Goose%20released%20a%20strategic%20plan%20that%20included%20three%20focus%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20accelerating%20growth%20among%20women%20and%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20building%20its%20direct-to-consumer%20network%2C%20and%20creating%20new%20products%20while%20expanding%20existing%20categories.%20The%20goal%20is%20for%20revenue%20to%20hit%20%242.1%20billion%20by%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20a%20wholesale%20brand%20for%20so%20long%2C%20and%20we%20decided%20that%20we%20wanted%20to%20have%20direct%20relationships%20with%20our%20consumers.%20We%20wanted%20to%20sell%20online%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20have%20stores%2C%26quot%3B%20Reiss%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Canada%20goose%20store%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792a9ca2fcded5e907486c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECanada%20Goose%20is%20expanding%20its%20direct-to-consumer%20channels%2C%20including%20by%20opening%20more%20retail%20stores.%3Cp%3ERob%20Kim%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDTC%20can%20be%20a%20powerful%20tool%20for%20controlling%20a%20brand's%20image%20and%20pricing%20and%20for%20attracting%20customers%20to%20other%20products.%20A%20department%20store%20may%20only%20carry%20Canada%20Goose's%20most%20popular%20parkas%3B%20a%20Canada%20Goose%20store%20or%20its%20website%20could%20have%20the%20full%20line.%20Plus%2C%20it%20allows%20the%20brand%20to%20understand%20its%20customers%20better%2C%20collect%20data%2C%20and%20improve%20client%20relationships%2C%20Prandelli%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20hasn't%20entirely%20worked.%20While%20DTC%20revenue%20was%20up%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%202024%2C%20it%20fell%20last%20quarter%20year%20over%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brand%20has%20attempted%20to%20diversify%20beyond%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fstyle%2Fbest-winter-dress-coats-for-women%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewinter%20parka%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20pushing%20customers%20to%20buy%20multiple%20parkas%2C%20which%20most%20people%20don't%20really%20need%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fem%3E%20since%202015%2C%20when%20it%20introduced%20its%20first%20spring%20collection.%20In%20response%20to%20questions%20about%20its%20stock%20performance%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20pointed%20to%20the%20company's%20expansion%20into%20other%20categories%2C%20including%2C%20most%20recently%2C%20eyewear%20(they%20didn't%20comment%20on%20the%20share%20price).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20iconic%20pieces%20never%20go%20out%20of%20the%20market%20and%20should%20be%20part%20of%20every%20collection%2C%26quot%3B%20Prandelli%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Canada%20Goose's%20jackets.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you%20need%20to%20have%20some%20continual%20injection%20of%20new%20items.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20much%20cheaper%20to%20make%20money%20from%20existing%20clients%20than%20keep%20attracting%20new%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20diversification%20attempts%20have%20been%20mixed.%20Sales%20of%20non-heavyweight-down%20units%20%E2%80%94%20including%20apparel%2C%20wind%20wear%2C%20and%20footwear%20%E2%80%94%20were%20up%2020%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20the%202025%20fiscal%20year%20and%20made%20up%2046%25%20of%20sales%20in%20fiscal%202024.%20(The%20move%20away%20from%20down%20is%20also%20a%20win%20for%20PETA%2C%20which%20has%20protested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-goose-jackets-fur-free-by-the-end-of-2022-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanada%20Goose's%20use%20of%20fur%20and%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20stopped%20using%20fur%20in%202022.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20Canada%20Goose%20still%20leans%20heavily%20on%20its%20signature%20item%3B%20for%20the%202024%20fiscal%20year%2C%20nearly%2080%25%20of%20its%20annual%20EBITDA%20came%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20which%20ends%20in%20December%2C%20when%20customers%20are%20shelling%20out%20on%20thick%20winter%20jackets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20luxury%20outerwear%20brands%2C%20like%20Moncler%2C%20collaborations%20have%20been%20one%20way%20to%20attract%20repeat%20customers.%20Canada%20Goose%20is%20attempting%20something%20similar%20by%20appointing%20Haider%20Ackermann%2C%20the%20French%20fashion%20designer%20who%20also%20heads%20design%20at%20Tom%20Ford%2C%20as%20creative%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20first%20collection%2C%20released%20in%20November%2C%20achieved%20%26quot%3Brecord-setting%20marketing%20success%2C%20and%20his%20new%20capsule%20collection%2C%20Snow%20Goose%20by%20Canada%20Goose%2C%20has%20been%20exceptionally%20well-received%20by%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Canada%20Goose%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20though%20did%20not%20provide%20sales%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAchieving%20luxury%20is%20one%20thing.%20Maintaining%20growth%20in%20the%20sector%2C%20though%2C%20may%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20a%20wild%20goose%20chase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-goose-status-symbol-outerwear-luxury-jacket-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737795781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6792a93d10c98eace913b873%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-goose-status-symbol-outerwear-luxury-jacket-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Canada%20Goose%2C%20famous%20for%20its%20luxury%20parkas%2C%20is%20a%20celebrity%20favorite.%20Here's%20how%20it%20went%20from%20making%20Antarctic%20outerwear%20and%20where%20it%20goes%20from%20here.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mberg%40businessinsider.com%20(Madeline%20Berg)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-goose-status-symbol-outerwear-luxury-jacket-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20make%20money%20from%20a%20TikTok%20hit.%20(Hint%3A%20You%20won't%20get%20it%20from%20TikTok.)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Comedian%20Rachel%20Coster%20stars%20in%20Boy%20Room%2C%20a%20TikTok%20hit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6793f0bfeb4be2fff9a217d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BBoy%20Room%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20hit%20TikTok%20show%20that%20features%20comedian%20Rachel%20Coster%20visiting%20miserable%20places%20where%20young%20men%20live.%20Amazon%20is%20sponsoring%20the%20second%20season%20of%20the%20show%2C%20which%20is%20owned%20by%20Gymnasium%2C%20a%20TikTok-centric%20digital%20media%20studio.%3Cp%3ELeeban%20Farah%2FGymnasium%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETikTok!%20It's%20still%20here%20in%20the%20US.%20That's%20good%20news%20for%20creators%20that%20make%20money%20working%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExcept%3A%20Most%20successful%20creators%20see%20very%20little%20money%20from%20TikTok%20itself.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGymnasium%20cofounder%20Adam%20Faze%20explains%20how%20to%20turn%20TikTok%20eyeballs%20into%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20ago%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-trump-law-apple-google-oracle-app-store-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20disappeared%20in%20America.%20Then%20it%20was%20back%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20looks%20like%20it%20will%20stay%20that%20way%2C%20for%20at%20least%20a%20month%20or%20two%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20the%20legal%20questions%20around%20its%20existence%20remain%20%E2%80%A6%20fuzzy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20good%20news%20for%20Adam%20Faze%2C%20who%20makes%20his%20living%20on%20TikTok.%20Faze%20co-founded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40itsgymnasium%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGymnasium%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20content%20studio%20that%20specializes%20in%20TikTok%20videos%2C%20with%20some%20success%3A%20Perhaps%20you've%20seen%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40boyroomshow%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoy%20Room%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20can-you-believe-this-filth%20tour%20of%20young%20men's%20...%20terrible%20living%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20season%20of%20%26quot%3BBoy%20Room%26quot%3B%20was%20a%20viral%20hit%20for%20Faze.%20But%20Faze%20says%20his%20company%20made%20almost%20zero%20dollars%20from%20its%20popularity.%20(Then%20again%2C%20it%20didn't%20spend%20much%2C%20either%3A%20Faze%20says%20each%20episode%20involved%20a%20crew%20of%20three%20people%20and%20cost%20around%20%242%2C000%20for%20a%20two-minute%20show.)%20The%20money%20is%20coming%20in%20the%20second%20season%20of%20%26quot%3BBoy%20Room%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20sponsoring%2C%20and%20which%20will%20feature%20hints%20on%20ways%20to%20fix%20your%20Boy%20Room%20%E2%80%94%20which%20will%20involve%20buying%20things%20from%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20talked%20to%20Faze%20this%20week%20because%20there's%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20discussion%20about%20how%20important%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-influencers-are-tired-angry-cautiously-hopeful-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20is%20to%20creators%20and%20influencers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20make%20money%20on%20TikTok.%20But%20there's%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20discussion%20about%20how%20that%20actually%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TLDR%3A%20Being%20popular%20on%20TikTok%20doesn't%20translate%20to%20making%20money%20on%20TikTok%2C%20since%20TikTok%20doesn't%20routinely%20share%20its%20advertising%20money%20with%20its%20creators%20(the%20only%20TikTok%20competitor%20that%20actually%20does%20this%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%3C%2Fa%3E).%20The%20way%20to%20make%20money%20on%20TikTok%20is%20to%20make%20something%20popular%20that%20brands%20will%20want%20to%20be%20associated%20with%2C%20and%20work%20out%20deals%20with%20them%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20an%20edited%20excerpt%20of%20my%20conversation%20with%20Faze.%20You%20can%20hear%20the%20whole%20thing%20on%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fchannels-with-peter-kafka%2Fid1080467174%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChannels%3C%2Fa%3E%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBusiness%20Insider%3A%20Why%20start%20a%20business%20focused%20on%20TikTok%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20any%20other%20video%20platform%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdam%20Faze%3A%20It's%20the%20quickness%20of%20how%20we're%20able%20to%20see%20if%20we%20have%20a%20hit%20or%20not.%20On%20TikTok%2C%20we%20usually%20know%20within%20the%20first%20three%20episodes%20we%20post%20if%20we%20have%20a%20successful%20show.%20That%20algorithm%20is%20just%20so%20phenomenal%20at%20defining%20who%20would%20or%20would%20not%20like%20something%20that%2C%20for%20us%2C%20it%20just%20is%20a%20no-brainer%20to%20test%20shows%20%5Bon%20TikTok%5D%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20make%20money%20from%20a%20viral%20hit%20on%20TikTok%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefit%20of%20coming%20into%20the%20space%20years%20after%20TikTok%20was%20introduced%20is%20we%20never%20revolved%20our%20business%20model%20around%20%26quot%3BHow%20much%20is%20TikTok%20going%20to%20pay%20us%3F%26quot%3B%20We%20went%20into%20this%20company%20thinking%20we%20would%20never%20make%20a%20dollar%20from%20any%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20probably%20generated%20about%20a%20half%20a%20billion%20views%20on%20TikTok%20since%20the%20company%20started.%20I%20think%20we've%20maybe%20made%20less%20than%20%2420%2C000%20from%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYouTube%20remains%20the%20only%20big%20video%20platform%20that%20consistently%20shares%20ad%20revenue%20with%20creators.%20Instagram%2C%20Snapchat%2C%20TikTok%20do%20not.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%2C%20short-form%20content%20is%20a%20great%20ad%20business%20for%20the%20platform.%20It's%20not%20for%20the%20creator%20%E2%80%94%20except%20for%20things%20now%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-tiktok-shop-is-changing-e-commerce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20Shop%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20you%20have%20individual%20creators%20who%20are%20making%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20month%20off%20of%2C%20basically%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D1bce1f2737a676f4ba1fddc9b64863d9258c58d9b29650b47372045a8d924334%26postID%3D6793ef67e2829faf19f94abd%26postSlug%3Dtiktok-money-explained-boy-room-adam-faze-peter-kafka-podcast-2025-1%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.qvc.com%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQVC%3C%2Fa%3E%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20TikTok's%20opinion%20has%20always%20been%20that%20you%20use%20our%20platform%20to%20make%20a%20name%20for%20yourself%2C%20to%20become%20a%20star%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20you%20will%20find%20other%20ways%20to%20monetize%20off%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you%20often%20hear%20creators%20talking%20about%20a%20brand%20deal.%20What%20does%20that%20mean%20in%20TikTok%20terms%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20your%20regular%2C%20everyday%20influencers%20that%20have%20a%20following%2C%20fashion%20companies%20and%20airlines%20and%20theme%20parks%20are%20going%20to%20sponsor%20that%20influencer.%20They'll%20tell%20them%20to%20make%20a%20video%20and%20they'll%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%20here's%20%2430%2C000%2C%20go%20make%20a%20video%20in%20the%20style%20that%20you%20normally%20would.%20And%20just%20be%20supportive%20of%20the%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMention%20us%20in%20some%20way%20and%20show%20off%20the%20product.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20us%2C%20we%20really%20want%20to%20find%20truly%20organic%20ways%20of%20bringing%20a%20sponsor%20into%20our%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20said%20you%20can%20figure%20out%20if%20a%20show%20is%20a%20hit%20after%20three%20episodes.%20Do%20you%20have%20hunches%20prior%20to%20that%3F%20Did%20you%20think%20%26quot%3BBoy%20Room%26quot%3B%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20hit%2C%20or%20was%20it%20just%20random%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20only%20release%20things%20we're%20a%20fan%20of.%20So%20we%20always%20have%20a%20hunch%20that%20we%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20work.%20Out%20of%20the%20six%20shows%20%5Bwe've%20made%5D%20they%20actually%20were%20all%20a%20success%2C%20viewership-wise.%20Sometimes%20they%20were%20just%20very%20hard%20to%20monetize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20that%20is%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20what%20allows%20us%20to%20greenlight%20shows%20%E2%80%94%20do%20we%20think%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20make%20money%20on%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20not%20just%20%26quot%3BWill%20people%20watch%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3BIs%20this%20something%20an%20Amazon%20or%20someone%20else%20would%20sponsor%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20give%20you%20an%20example.%20We%20used%20to%20make%20a%20show%20called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40clockworkdynasty%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClockwork%20Dynasty%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20with%20these%20two%20watch%20dealers%20from%2047th%20Street%20who%20are%20dear%20friends%20to%20this%20day.%20It%20was%20basically%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Fshows%2Fpawn-stars%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPawn%20Stars%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20We%20built%20their%20watch%20shop%20in%20our%20office.%20People%20would%20come%20on%20the%20show%20and%20buy%2C%20sell%2C%20trade%2C%20luxury%20watches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20show%20had%20a%20consistent%201%20million-plus%20viewers%20an%20episode.%20But%20our%20audience%20was%2099%25%20boys%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2018%20and%2024%2C%20which%20in%20the%20watch%20space%20isn't%20that%20monetized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey're%20not%20buying%20luxury%20watches.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20a%20show%20like%20that%2C%20sometimes%20you%20have%20to%20do%20the%20math.%20Unfortunately%2C%20it%20didn't%20make%20sense%20for%20us%20to%20keep%20making%20the%20show%2C%20even%20though%20we%20love%20it%20and%20people%20love%20it%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-money-explained-boy-room-adam-faze-peter-kafka-podcast-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22pu